parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel gauge can cause the rider to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to potential accidents or stranding.
symptoms: The fuel gauge drops to empty when the tank is still 3/4 full
the gauge displays full when the tank is empty
the gauge displays incorrect readings
the gauge is inconsistent and unpredictable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel module flange can cause the engine to hesitate, stutter, and lose power, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The engine hesitates
stutters
and loses power
especially during partial throttle and partial engine load
the vehicle becomes unstable and potentially dangerous.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine mounting system can cause the engine to shift or detach from the vehicle, leading to loss of control, accidents, or damage to surrounding components.
symptoms: The engine mounts break or detach
the engine shifts or moves excessively
the vehicle vibrates or shakes
the engine noise increases
the vehicle becomes difficult to handle or control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected lock-up of the front brakes can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and even fatalities.
symptoms: The front brakes lock up without warning
the vehicle's front wheel(s) suddenly seize
the vehicle loses control or stability
the rider is thrown off or falls over.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Brake System Diagnosis and Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships or repair shops to properly diagnose and repair brake system issues can lead to continued safety risks, financial burdens, and erosion of trust in the manufacturer and its representatives.
symptoms: The dealership or repair shop is unable to diagnose the problem
the dealership or repair shop blames the rider or owner
the dealership or repair shop charges for unnecessary repairs
the dealership or repair shop fails to provide a satisfactory solution.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the engine to jerk, leading to reduced control and increased risk of accidents, as well as excessive fuel consumption, resulting in increased costs and environmental impact.
symptoms: The engine jerks or stumbles
the motorcycle dies frequently
excessive fuel consumption
difficulty riding the motorcycle safely.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: High Wind Sensitivity Due to Solid Wheels
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The motorcycle's solid wheels can catch wind like a sail, making it prone to being blown off course, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The motorcycle is difficult to control in windy conditions
the motorcycle is blown off course
the motorcycle is unstable in crosswinds
the rider struggles to maintain control.
